This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language models and natural language processing tasks such as reading comprehension, paraphrase detection, and sentiment analysis. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of deep bidirectional transformers for transfer learning and adaptation of models. 

Additionally, it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with language understanding and processing, which is a key area of AI research. 

The paper also mentions the reduction of training time, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with optimization and efficiency of neural networks. 

Finally, the paper could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it discusses the use of language models for tasks such as reading comprehension and paraphrase detection, which are relevant to information retrieval systems.
